description:
"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2

No episode on the 17th. For reasons.

There was no episode on the 17th. Kennedy kicks the night off talking about Hillary's ringing endorsement from her kid Chelsea. Chelsea thinks we just haven't seen enough of Hillary yet. Our party panel is here to discuss. (TOM SHILLUE, JOE DeVITO, KAYLEIGH McENANY) Democratic hopeful Martin o'Malley says there aren't enough debates on the Democratic side. Is the DNC shielding Clinton? Presidential candidate Bobby Jindal has been taking big swings at Donald Trump. Could it revive his campaign, or sink it?

Last years unrest in Ferguson prompted a lot of interest in police militarization. Some people involved with documentary Peace Officer are in studio to talk. DUB LAWRENCE (former sherrif), SCOTTT CHRISOPHERSON (Peace Officer director), and  BRAD BARDER (also a director of Peace Officer) talk Ferguson, police militarization, Dub's experiences, how to know when a police department has crossed a line, and what can we change. I wish this segment was longer.

TOPICAL STORM
Dizzy doggy
Tiny prankster
Pumpkin boat
Barista boogie down
Drunk photobomb.

Our panel is back. First topic - A federal judge has ruled that it's your constitutional first amendment right to drop an f-bomb. Two men in china have tried selling their kidneys to get a shiny new iPhone. People having sex with robots and people being against said sex.

Winner of American Ninja Warrior ISAAC CALDIERO is here to talk about his taking the Ninja Warrior championship, training, diets, road food, and his million dollar prize.

Nightcap: Kennedy actually agrees with something Obama said. He recently spoke at an Iowa town hall and spoke out against the PC atmosphere on college campuses.
